    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MME descriptor counter management in S1AP cleanup\n\n### Summary\nThe `s1ap_eNB_remove_mme_desc` function in the eNB S1AP module was not properly updating instance counters after removing all MME descriptors. This caused inconsistencies in the eNB's internal state tracking, leading to incorrect behavior during subsequent S1 setup attempts and potential resource leaks.\n\nWhen all MME connections were removed via `s1ap_eNB_remove_mme_desc`, the `s1ap_mme_nb`, `s1ap_mme_pending_nb`, and `s1ap_mme_associated_nb` counters were left at their previous values instead of being reset to zero. This mismatch caused the eNB application to incorrectly believe there were still active MME connections when none existed.\n\nThe fix ensures that after all MME descriptors are removed, the associated counters are properly reset to reflect the clean state. Similar counter management was also missing in the NGAP AMF cleanup function and has been addressed for consistency.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: Added counter reset logic in `s1ap_eNB_remove_mme_desc` to set all MME counters to 0 after descriptor removal\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_management_procedures.c`: Added counter reset logic in `ngap_gNB_remove_amf_desc` for consistency\n\n"
}